Section 4. )optional_ Docker Quickstart

8. Docker Overview
9. Docker Containers vs Images
10. Running Containers from DockerHub

 - overview
   - self-contained entire 'application', all dependencies
   - just needs to run in a Docker engine
   - will run the same, anywhere

- containers vs images
  - image : entire definition of a container
    - big binary file
    - running image : container
  - publish images
    - DockerHub
  - course uses existing images for the course
    - richardchesterwood
  - verify docker installed
    - docker from command line
    - Enterprise, Community {open source, free}
  - MacOS Docker for Desktop takes care of a lot of the installations / setup in the video

- running containers from DockerHub
  - docker
  - dlogin
  - docker images
  - docker image pull richardchesterwood/k8s-fleetman-webapp-angular:release0-5
  - docker images
  - docker container run -p 8080:80 -d  25be029
    - browser : localhost:8080
  - docker container ls
  - docker inspect ecstatic_stonebraker
  - docker ps -a
  - docker stop 1b1a5
  - docker ps -a
